Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.33,0:01:05.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When the northern lands \Nare sealed off by snow and ice,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:06.17,0:01:13.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the swans flee the cold and hunger \Nand leave the land they know, heading south.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.25,0:01:25.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Amid the cold, blizzards, and ice of the north, \Nto the animals struggling to survive,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:25.37,0:01:30.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,there came a mysterious prince \Nwho reached out to them with a gentle hand,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:30.26,0:01:32.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,though no one knew of his existence.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.42,0:01:45.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And this is a story about \Nthat Prince of the Snow Country,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.77,0:01:50.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the swans as they journeyed south,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.14,0:01:55.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the friendship surrounding \None boy in Japan's northern lands.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.08,0:02:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{Heave-ho! }
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.00,0:03:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{Okay, I got this! Go on, pass! - etc}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.65,0:03:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Gaiaman!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.54,0:03:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, don't space out! \NWe're starting!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.00,0:03:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, there it goes!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.67,0:03:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, get it, you dog! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.32,0:03:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What, again? That's the third time!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.57,0:03:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.58,0:03:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're always losing because of Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.18,0:03:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Koro's a way better player than Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.25,0:03:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Goichi, what's wrong? \NHeading home?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.96,0:03:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't sweat it too much. \NDon't be discouraged. Just keep playing.{discouraged might be too adult for kids. Don't be down, maybe?}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.39,0:03:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I gotta help out in the fields. \NLet's go, Koro!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.23,0:03:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tch, going home with the family dog, huh?! {meaning that the dog came to meet him from school}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.53,0:03:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about a wimpy kid! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.64,0:04:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, you won't die if you fall, \Nbut don't climb that high.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.94,0:04:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.59,0:04:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,From here, I can see Dad's boat real close.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.15,0:04:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki's got more energy than her brother.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.72,0:04:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.89,0:04:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma, let's go home! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.02,0:04:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Goichi?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.32,0:04:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm almost done. \NCould you take that basket back with you?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.43,0:04:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, he's coming back! \NDad's boat is coming home.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.73,0:04:29.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The summer sun shines on the sea,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.87,0:04:35.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the fishermen's lively voices echo\N over the waves, but only for a short while.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.41,0:04:39.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Before long, winter comes\N to the northern sea.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.00,0:04:53.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And with it, life in these poor fishing villages \Nalong the shores of the north country
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.96,0:04:59.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,presents many changes and harsh trials daily.{life faces? no, the villages face, or life presents}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.60,0:05:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, winter already, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.20,0:05:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I really hate winter. Don't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.47,0:05:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Once summer's over, fall comes, \Nand then winter in no time.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.48,0:05:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it's always been.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.58,0:05:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Even way, way before I was born.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.79,0:05:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that already.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.42,0:05:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.76,0:05:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, obviously.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.58,0:05:33.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Grandma was right.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.58,0:05:40.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even so, for Goichi and his little sister Yuki, \Nnothing was fun once winter drew near.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.19,0:05:43.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After the summer fishing season ended,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.95,0:05:48.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,their fisherman father had to work in a distant town.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.62,0:05:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does Dad have to go \Nto the city every winter?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.28,0:05:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can't catch fish in winter.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.69,0:05:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago we used to catch way more,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.30,0:06:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,enough to last all winter\N on the summer's earnings.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.30,0:06:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's snowing already.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.23,0:06:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's awfully early this year. \NAt this rate, the swans'll be here soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.06,0:06:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, it'll get cold in the city too.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.66,0:06:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure will.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.09,0:06:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Construction sites'll be freezing.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.70,0:06:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.94,0:06:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.13,0:06:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, I'm counting on you \Nto look after the house.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.64,0:06:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.27,0:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I worry about Goichi the most.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.34,0:06:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,For a boy, he's not very hardy. {lit: good genki}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.78,0:06:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Always stuck inside once winter comes.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.10,0:06:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he catches colds so easily.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.28,0:06:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He just really hates the cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.55,0:07:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish he was more like Takeshi\N over at the Yamadas'. {from the yamada family}{changed were to was: would a rural housewife know proper subjunctive?}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.72,0:07:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That bossy kid? {gaki daisho = kid shogun - means the leader of the local boys}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.22,0:07:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe, but he's tough and full of life.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.44,0:07:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.23,0:07:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like I'll be working \Nwith Yamada-san again this year.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.92,0:07:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, take care of yourself!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.48,0:07:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you too, Yuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.02,0:07:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You promised a souvenir for me last night.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.38,0:07:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.58,0:07:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For you too? All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.42,0:07:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, take care of Mom, \NGrandma, and Yuki, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.68,0:07:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine! Right, Koro?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.26,0:07:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with the waterworks? \NYou're a boy, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.08,0:07:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull yourself together!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.34,0:07:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because it's cold, \Ndon't glue yourself to the kotatsu! {the heated table}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.73,0:07:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what they say—\NKids belong in the wind. {proverb, lit: children are the kids of the wind}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.98,0:07:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.10,0:07:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Show more spirit! Come on!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.50,0:07:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, got it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.41,0:07:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's better.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.09,0:07:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad, don't slip and fall\N at the construction site!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.68,0:08:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, Takeshi, don't get carried away \Nwhile merrymaking and fall into the icy sea.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.04,0:08:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.82,0:08:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't make Mom worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.84,0:08:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! You can count on me!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.79,0:08:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.09,0:08:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, if it isn't Yamada Kyuu! {??? I assume kyu-san is father's name}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.56,0:08:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hey, Old Man Gen from the town office! {gen jiisan}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.23,0:08:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, didn't I tell you not to call me "old man"?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.00,0:08:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not that old yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.37,0:08:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Still as lively as ever.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.04,0:08:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Goichi's dad's with you too?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.64,0:08:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You boys sure work hard every year.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.91,0:08:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we're the ones who should thank you \Nfor looking after things while we're gone.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.58,0:08:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be counting on you again this year.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.25,0:08:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, let's skip the formalities.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.86,0:08:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect timing, actually. \NHop in, both of you. I'm heading to town.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.04,0:08:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take you to the station.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.23,0:08:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'd appreciate that.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.28,0:08:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to trouble you, \Nbut we'll take you up on it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.80,0:08:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it'll also be tough for you ladies \Nat home until spring. See you. {kaa-chan-tachi}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.60,0:08:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.48,0:09:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! There they are.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.97,0:09:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Swans!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.80,0:09:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They came all the way \Nfrom the north again this year.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.30,0:10:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. \NThis is Koro's first time seeing them.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.44,0:10:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He was born after the swans left last year.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.09,0:10:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're early this year, \Nand there seem to be more than usual.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.10,0:10:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We're always just missing each other, huh? {meaning that one comes as another leaves}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.18,0:10:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time we get back, \Nthe swans'll be heading north again.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.76,0:10:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.42,0:10:38.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,Swans are messengers of winter.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.70,0:10:42.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,They came back to this inlet again this year.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.76,0:10:50.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,How many times have we welcomed you here \Nand seen you off throughout the years?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.76,0:10:57.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As winter birds, swans migrate every year around November, {literal, maybe by "winter birds" they meant "migratory?"}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.66,0:11:02.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,traveling in groups from faraway northern lands \Nlike Siberia and northern North America...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.66,0:11:08.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to Japan, mainly Hokkaido \Nand northern Honshu. {honshu = main island of the Japanese archipelago}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.42,0:11:15.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,From the far north, \Nthey fly as much as 5,000 kilometers.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.21,0:11:19.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In addition to Japan, \Nsome also head to the U.S. Pacific coast,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.83,0:11:25.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Scandinavian peninsula, Europe, or China.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.72,0:11:30.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then around March the following year, \Nwith the coming of spring,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.42,0:11:33.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,they return once more to the northern lands.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.30,0:11:45.44,Announcer,,0,0,0,,Many areas in the Kanto region \Nhave already seen their first snow,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.44,0:11:49.70,Announcer,,0,0,0,,and this year, cold Siberian air moving south \Nis expected to linger for a long time.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.70,0:11:54.35,Announcer,,0,0,0,,According to the Meteorological Agency's long-term forecast, heavy snowfall is expected
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.35,0:11:57.72,Announcer,,0,0,0,,not only in Hokkaido, Tohoku, and Joushin'etsu, \Nbut also in northern Kanto. {not sure why he singled out joushinetsu, maybe I heard it wrong}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.72,0:12:03.86,Announcer,,0,0,0,,Unlike last year's mild winter, this year \Nis shaping up to be a long, cold winter nationwide.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.86,0:12:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even colder than last year? \NGimme a break...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.96,0:12:07.49,Announcer,,0,0,0,,And now, a forecast for each area.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.04,0:12:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans finally made it here, \Nand now they’ve got it rough too.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.97,0:12:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.69,0:12:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The kitchen firewood’s about gone.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.82,0:12:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow’s a day off. \NBring some in from under the eaves. {they store it in open cases next to the house, outside}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.44,0:12:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi doesn't want to \Nbecause it's so cold outside.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.18,0:12:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! You stay out of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.76,0:12:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, come! {koi}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.58,0:12:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, come!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.97,0:12:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Feeding the swans, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.07,0:12:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.17,0:12:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Bet it's beans again, Old Man Gen? {??? **** gen jiisan mo}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.21,0:12:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.11,0:12:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoops, my bad! \NMeant to say Gen-san.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.91,0:13:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to tell you? \NStop treating me like an old man.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.25,0:13:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, see? Even the swans are saying, \N"So young, so young." {probably the sound that swans make is "wake" in Japanese or something}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.89,0:13:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if you say so... {?? probs means "good way of thinking"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.13,0:13:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Gen-san, you're feeding them \Nas a thank-you, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.33,0:13:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot. I'm just worried about them.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.03,0:13:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad so many came, but I keep thinking about how they're going to feed themselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.77,0:13:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, \Na lot of them have cygnets this year.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.15,0:13:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.78,0:13:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going sledding on the hill\N behind the village. Wanna come?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.38,0:13:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm busy right now. \NMaybe next time.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.19,0:13:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Tch. You're such a wimp in the cold! {calls him the word for "person sensitive to the cold"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.19,0:13:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.36,0:13:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.26,0:13:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew! So cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.49,0:13:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi! Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.00,0:13:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? \NIt's freezing, so close it already!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.80,0:13:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It came into the yard!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.03,0:13:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What did?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.44,0:13:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A baby swan. {it takes a swan 2-4 years to reach maturity}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.04,0:14:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd it come all the way here?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.78,0:14:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.44,0:14:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it wants us to take it in? \NThen let's take care of it. {lit: keep it at home}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.68,0:14:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's eating Koro's leftover food.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.62,0:14:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Cute!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.93,0:14:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's gone!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.93,0:14:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Koro, you idiot!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.50,0:14:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go see.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.47,0:14:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.57,0:14:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Koro, no!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.58,0:14:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gone already.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:40.91,0:14:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd it go?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.28,0:14:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.65,0:14:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It was eating the crackers \NI left here this morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.55,0:14:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't really have to run away.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.42,0:14:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It probably went back to the inlet.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.86,0:14:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.92,0:14:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Brr, cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.01,0:14:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.88,0:15:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.97,0:15:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.90,0:15:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what is it now?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.17,0:15:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.34,0:15:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right, the crackers!{This is definitely the wrong word for a US audience. In the US, crackers are a type of roll, ie, buttermilk crackers, and the children are feeding the swan either cookies or crackers.}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.57,0:15:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The crackers, hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.72,0:15:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.33,0:15:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, eat.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.71,0:15:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You dummy!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.40,0:15:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't do it gently, so the swan thought \Nyou were throwing something at it.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.83,0:15:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now it's personal. {lit: if it came to this, it's about determination}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.60,0:15:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.88,0:15:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.52,0:15:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It ran away again.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.49,0:15:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Tch. It's making fun of us.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.82,0:16:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, this time for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.00,0:16:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, take it...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.00,0:16:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.47,0:16:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, little swan!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.48,0:16:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice, tasty crackers.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.67,0:16:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's be friends, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.49,0:16:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There, there.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.54,0:16:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There, there!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.39,0:16:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, take it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.22,0:16:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, come.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.52,0:16:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, take it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.52,0:16:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.89,0:16:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, that's it, keep it up!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.43,0:16:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, it's good.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.02,0:16:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.92,0:16:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.18,0:16:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We were so close.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.81,0:16:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why's he riding a bike out here anyway?{I know Japanese doesn't have subjects, but this is not how kids speak}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.11,0:16:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So mean. I'm telling the police!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.22,0:16:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.55,0:16:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.13,0:17:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now, it {\i1}is{\i0} the police.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.55,0:17:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, if it isn't Goichi and Yuki-chan!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.60,0:17:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, you scared me.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.06,0:17:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... Guess I messed that up, huh.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.20,0:17:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That one was born up north this year \Nand came here for the first time.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.77,0:17:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's probably not used to people yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.72,0:17:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Goichi, you're sweating, \Nand you don't even have a coat or scarf on.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.25,0:17:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I jumped right out \Nfrom under the kotatsu and totally forgot.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.88,0:17:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? That's rare for our cold-sensitive Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.96,0:17:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The forecast said a blizzard will start tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.22,0:17:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful. See you!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.51,0:17:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.53,0:17:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it won't let up tomorrow either.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.90,0:17:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The blizzard?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.17,0:17:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... The real bitter cold comes later in the year. {???? her provincial accent is impenetrable to me}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.14,0:18:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Every few years, \Nthere's a freezing-cold winter like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.01,0:18:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans came all this way, \Nand it's still a hard winter for them.{Yes, the Japanese has 'swans' later, but again, English needs the subject first}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.71,0:18:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean food?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.06,0:18:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. \NSwans are winter birds, {same as before}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.73,0:18:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so unless they're really old, \Nthey don't usually freeze to death,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.43,0:18:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but the cold, snow, and ice \Ntake away all their food.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.77,0:18:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, a baby swan came all the way \Nto our yard looking for food today.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.58,0:18:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.96,0:18:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That baby swan must've been hungry.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.82,0:18:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That baby swan was really cute.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.79,0:18:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Its eyes were so clear! {kuriin}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.54,0:18:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.76,0:18:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the black spot by its beak \Nwas wider than the others. {other swans}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.53,0:18:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember it clearly!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.26,0:18:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, we'll be friends for sure, right? {meaning that it'll become used to them}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.27,0:18:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, Yuki! \NLet's name it Hanaguro. {hanaguro = literally "nose black" - maybe translate it in subs for clarity?}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.55,0:18:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.07,0:19:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a funny name.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.88,0:19:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the blizzard lets up, let's go see it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.55,0:19:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.88,0:19:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we can, not in this freezing snow.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.39,0:19:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, when it's warm in spring or summer, \Nwith lots of pretty flowers blooming,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.16,0:19:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we could play with Hanaguro then.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.17,0:20:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They all look weak.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.08,0:20:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing like the other day.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.05,0:20:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't eaten since the blizzard hit.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.82,0:20:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they want to, \Nthe snow and ice won't let them.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.39,0:20:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, they'll die.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.77,0:20:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, look, that's Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.57,0:20:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think it's dead?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.92,0:20:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Yuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.57,0:20:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.31,0:20:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're alive.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:47.51,0:20:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, crackers.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.88,0:20:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.15,0:20:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.02,0:20:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you don't have to run away!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.12,0:20:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.24,0:21:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, eat!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.57,0:21:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It a— {probably?}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.35,0:21:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, have more.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.38,0:21:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, let me try too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:25.58,0:21:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.09,0:21:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, there you go! Come!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.41,0:21:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There, you guys have some too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.97,0:21:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat, Hanaguro-chan.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.74,0:21:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still being cautious, \Nbut it'll get used to us soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.74,0:21:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, with this many swans, \Ncrackers won't cut it.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.16,0:21:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the town office!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.95,0:21:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you talk to Old Man Gen at the office, \Nhe might give you something.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.28,0:22:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it's rare for cold-fearing Goichi\N to come out because of the swans.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.39,0:22:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,See ya!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.20,0:22:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, figures.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:12.18,0:22:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I clean this up, \NI was thinking of heading over anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:17.00,0:22:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.79,0:22:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as they arrived, \Nthey got hit with two blizzards in a row.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:22.34,0:22:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, they'll all die.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:24.51,0:22:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor things.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:26.30,0:22:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the swans are guests \Nfrom faraway lands.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:31.12,0:22:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But most of the men are away working, \Nand those left behind are busy.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:36.62,0:22:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't just worry about swans all day here.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:40.51,0:22:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:41.69,0:22:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:43.01,0:22:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:44.38,0:22:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You will?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:47.82,0:22:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then. There are some sacks of dried corn \Nin the shed out back. Take one.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:53.46,0:22:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:54.44,0:22:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:55.11,0:22:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:57.38,0:23:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you can use the sled! \NJust make sure you don't catch a cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:03.12,0:23:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Come! Come!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:16.46,0:23:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, eat.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:19.33,0:23:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, please! Hanaguro, you meanie!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:32.58,0:23:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:33.95,0:23:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:35.68,0:23:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we clear the snow \Naround the feeding area.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.59,0:23:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only shovel this much with a sled.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.76,0:23:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help too!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.67,0:23:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.46,0:24:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it, move it!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:03.74,0:24:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm beat.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:04.71,0:24:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least the ground's showing a little.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:06.85,0:24:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better than being on top of ice.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:08.81,0:24:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, we'll break the ice next.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:11.05,0:24:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:17.91,0:24:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As usual, Koro couldn't wait! {flustered person; hasty person​}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:19.93,0:24:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:23.81,0:24:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:26.57,0:24:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't break.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:34.04,0:24:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:35.51,0:24:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked, Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:37.54,0:24:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, next one.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:42.34,0:24:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:44.48,0:24:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:46.62,0:24:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit nagging. I got it.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:49.47,0:24:54.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Goichi and Yuki worked \Nas hard as they could for the swans.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:58.60,0:25:05.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, by evening, the swans \Nseemed to have regained a bit of their strength.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:11.86,0:25:16.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But Goichi and Yuki \Nwere completely worn out.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:17.72,0:25:20.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And that night...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:22.59,0:25:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm beat today. \NBut somehow, it feels good.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:26.33,0:25:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro never did come\N close to us, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:30.13,0:25:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it just dislikes you. {?}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:32.33,0:25:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:33.73,0:25:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That swan's just stubborn. {contrary person; sourpuss; dog-in-the-manger probably, tho not sure how it explains anything}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:35.63,0:25:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't come near you either.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:37.77,0:25:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:49.95,0:25:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:51.75,0:25:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? I thought I heard a voice outside.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:01.96,0:26:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's this?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:04.40,0:26:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, this blizzard isn't cold at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:09.08,0:26:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:10.55,0:26:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for startling you.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:13.27,0:26:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi-kun, I am the Prince of the Snow Country, \Ndeep in the northern tundra.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:18.39,0:26:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A prince? You really {\i1}are{\i0} a prince!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:23.32,0:26:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So... why would a prince be here?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:26.25,0:26:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for being kind to the swans.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:29.92,0:26:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to thank you for that.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:33.43,0:26:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Not at all...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:34.84,0:26:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And also to become friends with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:37.78,0:26:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's wonderful!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:39.83,0:26:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:41.07,0:26:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's settled. We're friends now.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:43.26,0:26:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:44.22,0:26:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's your Snow Country like?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:47.22,0:26:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the homeland of the swans \Nthat come to that inlet.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.23,0:26:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So then... the place where Hanaguro was born?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:54.08,0:26:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to see it?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:54.95,0:26:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But isn't it cold?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.48,0:26:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine if you're with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.56,0:27:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, beautiful!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:10.88,0:27:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, hop on.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:12.56,0:27:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:20.37,0:27:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! My house looks so tiny now.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:41.31,0:27:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In winter, riding the north wind, \Nthe Snow Country spreads wider and wider.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:46.58,0:27:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When everything is sealed\N in deep snow and ice,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:54.04,0:27:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,animals lose their food, \Nand some can no longer survive there.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:01.53,0:28:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why the swans come\N to our land during that time?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:05.62,0:28:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:07.47,0:28:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are animals that stay behind \Nin the Snow Country,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.39,0:28:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and when the cold is too severe, \Nsome collapse and perish.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:16.98,0:28:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I ride the blizzards to help them.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:52.26,0:28:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:57.72,0:29:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi-kun, this year's cold wave \Nis especially harsh,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:02.04,0:29:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so I must travel to many Snow Countries \Nto help the animals.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:06.73,0:29:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Until spring comes and the swans depart \Nfor their northern home, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:12.12,0:29:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But... can I really do it? The way you put it\N takes away all my confidence.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:17.19,0:29:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you can. \NI know you will.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:22.51,0:29:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi-kun, what do you think \Nis the most important part of that job?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:26.52,0:29:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think... making sure the swans \Nhave food and don't get too cold?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:31.88,0:29:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course, that's also part of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:34.02,0:29:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's something even more important.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:36.91,0:29:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,More important?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:41.88,0:29:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I know!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:43.82,0:29:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Like when you helped the reindeer \Nand the bear cub. It's caring! {/giving them love}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:49.45,0:29:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's love, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:51.32,0:29:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. Yes, but is that all?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:58.02,0:29:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing...
Dialogue: 10,0:29:59.26,0:30:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:00.55,0:30:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...is courage.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:02.55,0:30:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:04.55,0:30:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. In order to truly love and care\N for the swans, you must have great courage.{was "are things you can only do if..." but was a three liner on my end}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:14.08,0:30:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:15.66,0:30:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Someday, you'll understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:30.30,0:30:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll meet again, Goichi-kun.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:32.10,0:30:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you for everything, Prince.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:34.85,0:30:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And please tell Yuki-chan, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:37.70,0:30:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll definitely become\N friends with Hanaguro.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:40.64,0:30:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:42.04,0:30:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hanaguro's very cautious \Nand shy around people.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:47.18,0:30:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro is an orphan.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:50.80,0:30:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:55.92,0:30:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why it came into our yard alone?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:59.26,0:31:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro was born last spring \Nin my country.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:11.22,0:31:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When winter drew near and it departed toward Japan, it was still with its father and mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:17.04,0:31:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But on the way, they were unlucky \Nand were attacked by a sea eagle, {Steller's sea eagle (Haliaeetus pelagicus)​}
Dialogue: 10,0:31:27.50,0:31:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and Hanaguro's parents were killed.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:31.46,0:31:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Hanaguro made it here.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:36.30,0:31:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so sad.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:38.01,0:31:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If grown-up Hanaguro flies back safely\N from here to the northern lands next spring,
Dialogue: 10,0:31:43.70,0:31:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure its late parents will be happy.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:47.77,0:31:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:48.94,0:31:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise I'll send Hanaguro \Nback to your country in the spring.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:52.64,0:31:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do my very best!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:54.66,0:31:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:56.01,0:31:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you promise me?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:58.48,0:31:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:00.15,0:32:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:01.22,0:32:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting for it eagerly in the North.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:03.42,0:32:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:04.22,0:32:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 10,0:32:36.15,0:32:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:37.59,0:32:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've met with the {\i1}real{\i0} Prince of the Snow Country \Nand made a promise to him!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:41.33,0:32:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a big boy already,\N yet you're still having dreams like that? {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:44.80,0:32:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd become friends with Hanaguro too.\NIsn't that what the Prince said?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:49.73,0:32:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'd been hoping \Nthat would happen all along, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:54.31,0:32:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you had that dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:56.04,0:33:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you it wasn't a dream! \NWhy is everyone teasing me now?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:00.01,0:33:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, I'll be late for school. \NThanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:02.58,0:33:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:04.35,0:33:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it was a dream. {Grandma }
Dialogue: 10,0:33:07.22,0:33:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:08.92,0:33:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, dream or not, it's a nice story.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:12.39,0:33:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, more importantly, even if it was a dream, \Na promise is a promise.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:16.16,0:33:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:17.33,0:33:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I promised, didn't I?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:20.57,0:33:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Goichi, you've got to take care of the swans,\N with all your strength, in the Prince's place.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:27.82,0:33:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:30.78,0:33:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm off!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:33.58,0:33:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Prince of the Snow Country?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:39.43,0:33:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impressive, all right! \NFlying through the sky with a prince!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:43.06,0:33:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna have a dream like that too. \NRight, guys?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:49.16,0:33:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Goichi, what was the North Pole like? Tell us!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:53.33,0:33:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it so cold you forgot already?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:55.57,0:33:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:58.14,0:34:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with Goichi's grandma.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:01.55,0:34:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's teach.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:05.81,0:34:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, taking good care \Nof swans is a fine thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:09.18,0:34:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Best of luck, Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:11.02,0:34:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect timing, actually.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:12.25,0:34:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Next week in science class, let's study migratory birds, starting with swans.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:27.20,0:34:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi! Are these what you need? {lit: is this kind of stuff okay}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:31.40,0:34:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavy stuff... Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:33.51,0:34:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let me carry it.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:35.26,0:34:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:36.64,0:34:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can be helpful too sometimes, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:41.25,0:34:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew! It's cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:43.52,0:34:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, for someone who hates the cold, \Nyou're doing great.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:47.29,0:34:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:49.02,0:34:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All for a promise with the Prince?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:51.92,0:34:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right! Here, corn and breadcrumbs.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:56.14,0:35:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, perfect timing! \NWe just ran out today. Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:01.13,0:35:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yuki-chan, I hope you and Hanaguro \Nbecome friends soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:05.77,0:35:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:12.51,0:35:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Swan couples are very close.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:14.88,0:35:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They work together to build nests, \Nprotect their eggs, and raise their cygnets.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:20.39,0:35:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Fathers and mothers \Ntreasure their children deeply.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:23.86,0:35:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish {\i1}my{\i0} dad and mom could hear that.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:30.13,0:35:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a story said to have happened \Nat a certain lake in Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:33.80,0:35:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, a baby swan was trying \Nto land on the lake with its parents.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:38.94,0:35:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,By bad luck, it struck some power lines \Nand fell to the ground.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:45.98,0:35:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, a nearby farmer rescued \Nthe baby swan and treated its injuries at home,
Dialogue: 10,0:35:52.85,0:35:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but after that, it was never able to fly again.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:56.39,0:36:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,From that day on, the parent swans \Nstayed completely still,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:00.69,0:36:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes crying out sadly, \Nnever seeming to eat.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:19.85,0:36:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the next spring came.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:22.43,0:36:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans trained hard before returning north, \Ncircling high above the lake.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:38.60,0:36:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But the parent swans \Nwere the same as ever,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:42.18,0:36:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,remaining completely still.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:45.80,0:36:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,On a dry day when a proper north wind blew, \Nthe swans began to take off for the north.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:52.78,0:36:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, even the parents who had waited unmoving for their child took off with the flock.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:05.99,0:37:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mother, weakened too much \Nby their waiting, crashed near the shore.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:23.74,0:37:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The father swan, of course, and the other swans\N turned back to encourage her,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:29.51,0:37:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was no use. She died.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:37.59,0:37:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The father swan, longing for his \Nflightless child and his lost mate,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:41.89,0:37:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,never left the lake that year, they say.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:49.37,0:37:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even swans feel the same way \Nabout their children.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:53.69,0:37:59.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,So Hanaguro was separated from his parents \Nlike that and ended up all alone?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:01.71,0:38:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, eat.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:07.45,0:38:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:37.98,0:38:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, here.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:43.86,0:38:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on, eat.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:47.58,0:38:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:53.20,0:38:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he said. {??? can't hear the beginning}
Dialogue: 10,0:38:54.77,0:38:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... The Snow Country Prince asked him to?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:58.44,0:39:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Fancy dream he had. {omoshirei?}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:00.41,0:39:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He says it wasn't a dream, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:04.51,0:39:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning, Old Man Gen!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:05.84,0:39:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You're lively as ever, ringleader. {gaki daisho - kid shogun again}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:09.68,0:39:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki­chan!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:11.55,0:39:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I've got corn and breadcrumbs.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:13.96,0:39:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:14.96,0:39:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Hanaguro today?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:20.88,0:39:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yuki-chan...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:22.83,0:39:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hanaguro...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:31.00,0:39:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:33.31,0:39:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hanaguro...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:35.64,0:39:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro is...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:50.09,0:39:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Goichi...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:54.63,0:39:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeshi-chan, what should I do?
Dialogue: 10,0:40:10.07,0:40:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:14.31,0:40:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:16.70,0:40:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:19.75,0:40:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it, Yuki!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:23.42,0:40:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:29.23,0:40:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro... Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:32.66,0:40:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So it really wasn't a dream. \NThe Snow Country Prince...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:38.94,0:40:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:45.94,0:40:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just thinking about the look \Non your face today makes me laugh.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:53.82,0:40:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, if the Snow Country Prince comes again, \Nlet me meet him too.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:58.62,0:41:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:01.29,0:41:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Prince is busy traveling \Nto different snow countries, helping animals.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:07.37,0:41:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means we have to take care \Nof the swans here ourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:12.34,0:41:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. That's what I promised.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:14.37,0:41:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro's getting bigger and bigger too, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:17.27,0:41:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He's gray now, but over the winter, \Nhis feathers will slowly change,
Dialogue: 10,0:41:22.75,0:41:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and by the time he goes back to the Prince's land, \Nhe'll be much whiter, a proper swan.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:34.35,0:42:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the usual sound swans make.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:36.25,0:42:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on? \NKoro's crying too.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:54.01,0:42:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if something happened\N with this thunder and all...
Dialogue: 10,0:42:56.81,0:42:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When fields and mountains\N are closed by snow,
Dialogue: 10,0:42:59.60,0:43:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,swans aren't the only animals\N driven here by hunger.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:40.95,0:43:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Goichi, there!
Dialogue: 10,0:43:43.62,0:43:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:29.93,0:44:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You mutts! {konoyarou}
Dialogue: 10,0:44:32.52,0:44:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Take that! Take this!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:37.16,0:44:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:40.34,0:44:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:52.66,0:44:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro, are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:56.01,0:44:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:59.26,0:45:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:00.80,0:45:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the time to wait around!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:02.83,0:45:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry, go tell Gen-san at the town office!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:05.60,0:45:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:06.37,0:45:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You coward!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:17.68,0:45:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hadn't hesitated, \NHanaguro might've been fine!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:23.55,0:45:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who told you that just feeding him \Nand doting on him would be enough?!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:29.69,0:45:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Get going already!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:48.95,0:45:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's see.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:55.50,0:45:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it look like, doctor? {sensei}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:58.16,0:46:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This wing injury is worrying.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:00.51,0:46:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... it won't be able to fly again?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:05.42,0:46:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to tell you the truth, \NI'm no swan specialist...
Dialogue: 10,0:46:12.30,0:46:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but for now, let it rest like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:15.44,0:46:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You did the right thing bringing it inside. {looking after him}
Dialogue: 10,0:46:17.81,0:46:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's young, so the wound \Nshould close eventually.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:20.71,0:46:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, well, it'll depend on luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:24.22,0:46:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like some tea?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:25.85,0:46:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Ah, thank you kindly.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:29.79,0:46:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... do you think next spring \Nhe'll be able to fly north with the others?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:35.94,0:46:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That might be a little difficult.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:39.60,0:46:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a tough ask, Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:44.00,0:46:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Until swans grow up to adulthood, \Nthere are a lot of dangers.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:49.07,0:46:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if a hundred cygnets are born, \Nonly a third survive the first year.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:54.91,0:46:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,By the fourth year, only one-tenth remain.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:57.28,0:46:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So maybe around ten \Nout of a hundred make it.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:59.86,0:47:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and a swan with an injured wing \Nhas it especially hard.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:04.79,0:47:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, don't look so down.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:08.59,0:47:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid's been taking\N great care of the swans.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:12.91,0:47:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, he got incredibly\N attached to this one.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:16.73,0:47:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. So you're the one?
Dialogue: 10,0:47:19.67,0:47:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Give the medicine regularly, \Nand keep feeding him well.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:23.41,0:47:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Once he gets a bit stronger, letting him walk around the dirt floor will count as exercise. {literal}
Dialogue: 10,0:47:27.44,0:47:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When he starts moving his wings \Non his own, that's a good sign.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:30.82,0:47:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be careful about the cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:34.15,0:47:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll check in again.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:35.79,0:47:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Gen-san, give me updates \Nby phone now and then.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:38.66,0:47:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I will.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:41.19,0:47:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Next spring might be too soon, but... {for hanaguro to fly}
Dialogue: 10,0:47:48.87,0:47:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if its wings move \Nby around New Year's, then maybe...
Dialogue: 10,0:47:55.04,0:47:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't let yourself give up, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:48:11.09,0:48:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Koro, be quiet.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:13.36,0:48:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you bark at Hanaguro.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:18.86,0:48:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro, get better soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:25.00,0:48:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, Mom says it's time for bed.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:28.24,0:48:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:30.07,0:48:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For tonight, you should\N just let the bird be. {lit: leave things alone quietly}
Dialogue: 10,0:48:34.35,0:48:38.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,If only... If only I'd acted\N right away back then... {fought}
Dialogue: 10,0:48:42.24,0:48:44.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,You coward! You coward...
Dialogue: 10,0:48:46.41,0:48:51.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,Until swans grow up to adulthood, \Nthere are a lot of dangers.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:51.73,0:48:58.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,Even if a hundred cygnets are born, \Nonly a third survive the first year.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:40.26,0:49:47.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro's father and mother gave up everything to let Hanaguro live, even their own lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:50.77,0:49:58.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,Love, and truly caring for the swans, \Ncan only be done if you have great courage. {30:04}
Dialogue: 10,0:50:01.00,0:50:04.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see! That's what he meant!
Dialogue: 10,0:50:39.30,0:50:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Snow Country Prince!
Dialogue: 10,0:50:42.51,0:50:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 10,0:50:44.44,0:50:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 10,0:50:45.38,0:50:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I will keep my promise to you!
Dialogue: 10,0:50:49.25,0:50:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Next spring, along with the other swans, \NI'll make sure Hanaguro flies off to your land!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:09.83,0:51:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, come, come!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:31.21,0:51:35.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With school, Hanaguro, \Nand the swans of the inlet,
Dialogue: 10,0:51:35.69,0:51:39.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,there was no time left for Goichi \Nto cling to the kotatsu.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:39.86,0:51:44.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,No matter what, \Nhe had to heal Hanaguro's wing.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:44.33,0:51:49.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Goichi and Yuki worked tirelessly, caring for him together.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:52.24,0:51:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No! {dame}
Dialogue: 10,0:52:06.74,0:52:10.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Goichi dashed through the snow, \Ncheeks bright red.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:11.20,0:52:18.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And eventually, more and more classmates \Nand people in the village began cheering them on.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:18.97,0:52:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang in there.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:19.87,0:52:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:22.84,0:52:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:33.83,0:52:41.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro's body recovered so quickly \Nthat even Grandma and Gen-san were amazed.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:42.66,0:52:45.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But then one day...
Dialogue: 10,0:52:59.51,0:53:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Mom?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:02.38,0:53:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, just don't be too scared.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:05.02,0:53:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father got hurt at his job in town.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:09.48,0:53:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad did?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:11.31,0:53:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Goichi, there's no need \Nto worry that much.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:16.13,0:53:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, okay, Goichi?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:19.36,0:53:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,His life's not in danger, but he's hospitalized\N and won't be able to move around for a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:24.44,0:53:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For a while?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:25.84,0:53:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe until spring, maybe even longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:29.24,0:53:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't allow enough time for it to heal properly,
Dialogue: 10,0:53:32.39,0:53:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a risk he won't be able to walk.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:34.34,0:53:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So while he's hospitalized, \Nyour mom'll need to stay with him.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:47.03,0:53:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, you're going, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:49.73,0:53:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, Mom needs to be \Nwith Dad, who's injured.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:54.93,0:53:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:56.73,0:53:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:57.85,0:54:05.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Goichi felt like crying too, but he knew he couldn't show tears and make his mother worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:05.54,0:54:07.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's what Goichi thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:07.64,0:54:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, leave worrying about your dad to me. \NListen carefully to what Grandma says,
Dialogue: 10,0:54:13.37,0:54:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and take good care of the swans too, all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:54:17.86,0:54:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You promised the Snow Country \NPrince, remember?
Dialogue: 10,0:54:22.39,0:54:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 10,0:54:30.63,0:54:36.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After Mother left for the town hospital, \Nthe snowy days continued.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:18.48,0:55:21.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,Will Dad really get better?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:28.46,0:55:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Prince!
Dialogue: 10,0:55:30.26,0:55:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi-kun, moping like that \Ndoesn't suit you at all. {lit: if you're about to cry, that's odd}
Dialogue: 10,0:55:32.86,0:55:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you a Snow Country Prince too? {lit: of this snow country}
Dialogue: 10,0:55:34.80,0:55:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? A prince?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:36.45,0:55:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, a kind-hearted \Nprince of the swans.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:40.37,0:55:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But back then, I couldn't save Hanaguro.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:44.67,0:55:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi-kun...
Dialogue: 10,0:55:46.74,0:55:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage isn't just about \Nfighting enemies headlong.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:51.85,0:55:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage means not running away \Nwhen things are hard,
Dialogue: 10,0:55:54.89,0:55:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,not giving up when things hurt, \Nand never abandoning hope.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:59.79,0:56:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Never abandoning hope...
Dialogue: 10,0:56:02.79,0:56:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have courage like the sun \Nthat outshines everyone around,
Dialogue: 10,0:56:06.06,0:56:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your father will surely get better too.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:08.50,0:56:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like spring comes when the swans take flight, \Nspring will surely come to your family as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:12.99,0:56:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I understand, Prince.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:15.61,0:56:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then give my regards \Nto Yuki-chan and Hanaguro.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:18.01,0:56:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You're leaving already?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:20.68,0:56:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The animals of the snow country are waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:23.38,0:56:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When spring comes, I'll be waiting for Hanaguro \Nand the others in the northern land!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:31.49,0:56:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye! Thank you, Prince!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:38.96,0:56:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, isn't it lukewarm?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:40.96,0:56:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just right.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:45.52,0:56:49.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dad, Mom, please don't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:50.81,0:56:53.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,We'll all work together and do our best here.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:53.39,0:56:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Goichi's looking after the swans?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:57.71,0:57:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He's so engrossed in it, \Nhe's running all over even in the cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:02.02,0:57:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What, our cold-fearing Goichi? \NNow, that's quite something.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:06.39,0:57:09.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm not lonely anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:09.09,0:57:12.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dad, please do your best \Nand get better soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:12.96,0:57:16.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro will probably\N be able to fly soon too.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:21.17,0:57:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is Hanaguro?
Dialogue: 10,0:57:22.92,0:57:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The way Yuki draws it, \Nit looks like a duck. {domestic duck}
Dialogue: 10,0:57:25.74,0:57:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, hang this one too.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:27.61,0:57:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:28.93,0:57:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the reply letter \Nyou wrote to those two earlier,
Dialogue: 10,0:57:32.48,0:57:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,add a line saying, \N"Give my regards to Hanaguro."
Dialogue: 10,0:57:35.35,0:57:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:38.91,0:57:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, you're dropping so much.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:41.66,0:57:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Is boiled sweet potato that hard to eat? {???? maybe "mashed" but the others we see in the bowl aren't mashed; maybe it's something about eating from her hand versus the thing she does next}
Dialogue: 10,0:57:43.99,0:57:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then...
Dialogue: 10,0:57:50.30,0:57:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you ate it nice and clean!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:52.40,0:57:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it easier to eat this way?
Dialogue: 10,0:57:58.48,0:58:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro, you'll definitely fly.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:01.38,0:58:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll go with everyone in spring.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:03.58,0:58:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I wish you could stay here forever,
Dialogue: 10,0:58:06.82,0:58:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but I know you must return to the northern land, \Nthe Prince's country.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:11.76,0:58:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand, Hanaguro? \NYou do, don't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:23.93,0:58:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A swan shedding tears?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:27.54,0:58:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That Yuki... {maybe it's something about snow?}
Dialogue: 10,0:58:29.21,0:58:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But dear, you always say only humans \Ncry and laugh, don't you? {?? not sure who said that}
Dialogue: 10,0:58:35.01,0:58:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that really true?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:36.95,0:58:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe Yuki's letter. \NAnimals have hearts too.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:41.72,0:58:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yuki's feelings reached that heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:46.46,0:58:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I want to believe.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:48.66,0:58:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be it. \NHanaguro understood Yuki's feelings.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:56.47,0:59:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Come!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:16.92,0:59:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,With snow this deep, \Nbikes are useless now. Brr! {??? idk what that last uso bit is}
Dialogue: 10,0:59:24.61,0:59:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Even my rascal Takeshi? {naughty; mischievous; unruly}
Dialogue: 10,0:59:26.83,0:59:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Just last year, he was throwing snowballs at the swans,
Dialogue: 10,0:59:30.31,0:59:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and Gen-san came to me\N to complain about him.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:32.94,0:59:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:35.67,0:59:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's this?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:37.41,0:59:40.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro and Koro have\N become good friends,
Dialogue: 10,0:59:40.51,0:59:43.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,and sometimes they sleep\N cuddled up together.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:43.61,0:59:46.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,I think it's because it's warmer that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:46.52,0:59:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! A swan and a puppy together?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:49.92,0:59:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that something? Right, Mister? {otosan - probably yuki's father?}
Dialogue: 10,0:59:54.52,0:59:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Excuse me.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:59.93,1:00:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My, whenever letters from your children arrive, \Nyour fever goes down.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:04.43,1:00:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, seeing all this \Nmakes even me feel healthier.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:17.35,1:00:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,His feathers have gotten pretty white. \NHe'll be fine now, Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:21.49,1:00:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Soon we'll have to start flight practice.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:25.72,1:00:32.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But the harsh laws of nature \Nare not quite so forgiving. {lenient}
Dialogue: 10,1:00:32.88,1:00:42.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As full winter set in, the abnormal cold wave \Nfinally showed its true colors and began to rage.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:51.23,1:00:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still cold? \NJust endure it a little more.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:55.22,1:00:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, it's freezing!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:04.74,1:01:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared. \NI've never seen anything like this.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:07.03,1:01:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans outside must be suffering.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:09.60,1:01:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this has got to be the worst cold\N since Goichi was born.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:14.04,1:01:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans will need more than just \Na little endurance to get through this... {probably means that just "bearing with it a little" won't be enough - but her accent is still too much for me}
Dialogue: 10,1:01:51.84,1:01:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an experienced swan couple, \Nmaking the journey back and forth many times. {???? *** mou nandomo}
Dialogue: 10,1:01:56.81,1:01:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They barely made it here again this time.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:00.05,1:02:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they survived\N and flew off in the spring,
Dialogue: 10,1:02:02.85,1:02:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they probably wouldn't have made it back \Nto their northern homeland.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:11.43,1:02:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, they say this is the coldest \Nit's been in about ten years.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:24.36,1:02:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a rather small place, \Ncompared to Mother Siberia, {the grave}
Dialogue: 10,1:02:29.88,1:02:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but at least they went together. \NRest in peace.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:38.20,1:02:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, it could be that Hanaguro is the grandchild of these two, or even their great-grandchild.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:45.83,1:02:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, old m— {gen ji[san]}
Dialogue: 10,1:02:47.66,1:02:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... I mean, Gen-san.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:49.43,1:02:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They say once swans become a pair, \Nthey keep that bond for life.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:54.84,1:02:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And together, they protect their young.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:58.41,1:03:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the next mating season comes,
Dialogue: 10,1:03:00.31,1:03:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the young leave their parents \Nand become independent.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:05.40,1:03:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But the migration routes of parents and children \Nare said to still remain almost the same.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:11.25,1:03:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:12.49,1:03:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what you're saying is definitely possible.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:17.63,1:03:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, for this swan couple's sake too, \Ntake good care of Hanaguro.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:22.03,1:03:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:28.15,1:03:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't wanna eat? \NProbably because it's too cold.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:31.41,1:03:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang in there, spring's almost here.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:39.73,1:03:42.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The snow kept falling and stopping,
Dialogue: 10,1:03:42.99,1:03:45.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but the cold never let up,
Dialogue: 10,1:03:45.39,1:03:50.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the village was left trapped \Nin ice and snow.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:00.10,1:04:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi. Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:03.11,1:04:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hanaguro is dead.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:05.76,1:04:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:11.82,1:04:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:18.29,1:04:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not dead.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:19.69,1:04:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Its body's warm, and it's still breathing.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:21.92,1:04:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But it looks just like those swans that died.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:24.76,1:04:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's move it somewhere warmer.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:27.26,1:04:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma, light a fire in the hearth!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:29.20,1:04:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:44.61,1:04:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro! What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:47.12,1:04:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably some kind of illness.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:48.99,1:04:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We amateurs can't do anything, \Nand in this blizzard, we can't even call a vet. {meaning non-professionals}
Dialogue: 10,1:04:55.22,1:04:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it going to die?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:57.14,1:05:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but if it stays like this, probably.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:00.46,1:05:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess it just had bad luck. \NWe may have to give up.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:06.27,1:05:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:07.90,1:05:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If I get to the town office, \NGen-san will help with his jeep.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:10.57,1:05:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What... Goichi! Even if you go to the office, \Nin a blizzard like this...
Dialogue: 10,1:05:14.01,1:05:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't know unless you try!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:20.75,1:05:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There! That's why I told you to stop, Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:24.29,1:05:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:25.32,1:05:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit...
Dialogue: 10,1:05:26.69,1:05:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro! I'll definitely \Nbring a vet, so hang in there!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:31.66,1:05:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:43.19,1:05:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He actually went.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:45.54,1:05:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Reckless kid.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:47.21,1:05:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy who used to be such a wimp...
Dialogue: 10,1:06:21.64,1:06:25.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dammit... Like this could ever stop me!
Dialogue: 10,1:06:37.89,1:06:41.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,This time, I swear, I'll save Hanaguro.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:41.70,1:06:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{yelling}
Dialogue: 10,1:06:51.98,1:06:55.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right. Remember what the Prince said.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:56.38,1:06:57.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,Courage means...
Dialogue: 10,1:06:57.83,1:07:00.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,not running away when things are hard...
Dialogue: 10,1:07:05.22,1:07:08.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,Not giving up when things hurt...
Dialogue: 10,1:07:09.06,1:07:10.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,And never...
Dialogue: 10,1:07:10.63,1:07:13.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,Never abandoning hope!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:41.42,1:07:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This phone's dead too. \NAt this rate, we must be right out of luck. {lit: without luck, you can't help it/can't proceed}
Dialogue: 10,1:07:45.36,1:07:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone line along the way must've snapped. Nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:49.63,1:07:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just great. Heavy snow warning, \Nand we can’t even call anyone. {???? komatta naa *** ha deterutte no ni - no clue what's the missing part, but I think it's a shortening of yuki keihou - snow warning, so he probably says "I'm supposed to warn villagers/phone in the warning, but I can't"}
Dialogue: 10,1:07:54.34,1:07:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,1:07:56.27,1:07:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, just forget it for now \Nand have some tea.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:59.21,1:08:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If the snow stops by morning, \NI'll make the rounds with you again. {as the residential police box officer is supposed to}
Dialogue: 10,1:08:02.95,1:08:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But tonight's impossible.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:04.15,1:08:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Who just knocked? {??}
Dialogue: 10,1:08:05.58,1:08:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind, probably. \NWho'd ever be out in this blizzard?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:12.62,1:08:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the wind!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:19.40,1:08:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! It's a kid!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:20.61,1:08:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi! It's Goichi! \NWhat on earth are you doing out now?!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:24.93,1:08:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's warm him up.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:26.54,1:08:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, anyway?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:28.54,1:08:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Goichi! Stay with us!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:33.08,1:08:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Old Man Gen, please, hurry and get the vet!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:36.24,1:08:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The vet! Why?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:38.21,1:08:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro... Hanaguro is dying!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:42.45,1:08:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro? That swan?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:44.47,1:08:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And you came all the way here \Njust for that?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:51.48,1:08:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is tough...
Dialogue: 10,1:08:52.90,1:08:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to fetch a vet is fine, but the road to town \Nis under construction and full of potholes.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:57.93,1:09:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't get over \Nthe inlet {mountain }pass anymore.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:00.80,1:09:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A snowplow might come \Nby noon tomorrow, but until then...
Dialogue: 10,1:09:03.67,1:09:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If that'd be in time, would this kid have risked his life coming here in a blizzard like this?
Dialogue: 10,1:09:08.64,1:09:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter how tough your four-wheel-drive jeep is, in this storm...
Dialogue: 10,1:09:13.15,1:09:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You yourself just said it was impossible—
Dialogue: 10,1:09:16.05,1:09:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:17.05,1:09:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm an old man, all right?
Dialogue: 10,1:09:18.79,1:09:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen here, kid.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:20.32,1:09:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Even this little guy made it\N all the way here.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:22.83,1:09:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You think we adults can just sit back now?!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:25.63,1:09:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, you're right, but...
Dialogue: 10,1:09:27.16,1:09:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Then I'll do it on my own.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:29.67,1:09:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take the vet and this kid to Hanaguro \Nwhatever it takes... right now!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:47.48,1:09:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you drive a little more gently?
Dialogue: 10,1:09:50.54,1:09:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please bear with it, Doc. \NThis kid's promise to the Prince is on the line.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:00.16,1:10:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit...
Dialogue: 10,1:10:28.04,1:10:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there! {????? no clue maybe "not so fast!"}
Dialogue: 10,1:10:33.63,1:10:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on tight, or else you'll bite your tongue.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:37.10,1:10:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This ride's gonna get rough for a bit. {?????}
Dialogue: 10,1:10:43.41,1:10:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet when you treat him as an old man, \Nhe gets grumpy right away. {??? idk why he says that now}
Dialogue: 10,1:10:46.34,1:10:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You say something?!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:47.78,1:10:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say a word!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:12.74,1:11:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, with this, \Nwe can probably get through. {???}
Dialogue: 10,1:11:16.07,1:11:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure this is enough?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:17.74,1:11:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just get on.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:25.48,1:11:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That kid is crazy! \NIn a blizzard like this!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:29.15,1:11:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The roads are impassable \Neven to cars right now!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:33.79,1:11:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi? {? weird yell there, probably takeshi answering "yeah!" to grandma's "goichi?"}
Dialogue: 10,1:11:47.24,1:11:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:49.44,1:11:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I get it.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:10.98,1:12:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, young man. Take a listen.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:31.21,1:12:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beating! Stronger and stronger.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:35.08,1:12:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Goichi, let me listen too.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:41.56,1:12:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alive! It's alive!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:44.09,1:12:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thump, thump!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:51.50,1:12:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro...
Dialogue: 10,1:12:52.74,1:12:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:57.66,1:12:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be fine now.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:59.88,1:13:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a bit of a cold, really.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:02.81,1:13:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing we treated it tonight.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:05.35,1:13:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was badly weakened, after all.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:07.37,1:13:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If we'd been late, it could've turned into pneumonia.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:09.89,1:13:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, it'll be better in a week or so. {/or ten days}
Dialogue: 10,1:13:14.32,1:13:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You did great, kid.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:17.26,1:13:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro, good for you!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:19.20,1:13:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Goichi.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:20.93,1:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloody well done, Goichi!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:25.20,1:13:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's a relief.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:27.67,1:13:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, I drove that jeep like it was the last time \Nin my life, but it paid off in the end.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:32.74,1:13:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all about guts, courage!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:34.69,1:13:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true...
Dialogue: 10,1:13:36.65,1:13:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was going to die, though.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:38.28,1:13:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, damn right.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:40.88,1:13:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:09.60,1:14:13.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro's feathers are turning white, \Nand he's full of energy.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:13.32,1:14:15.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today, he went outside for the first time.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:15.70,1:14:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Well then, I can't let myself\N fall behind either.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:19.38,1:14:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, dear, reading these letters, \Ndoesn't it feel like Goichi's really changing?
Dialogue: 10,1:14:25.28,1:14:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so too?
Dialogue: 10,1:14:28.46,1:14:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing more mature, or maybe... {lit: becoming an adult}
Dialogue: 10,1:14:31.10,1:14:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like something solid \Nis taking root inside him, like a backbone. {??}
Dialogue: 10,1:14:37.54,1:14:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:39.89,1:14:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Snow Country Prince, huh.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:52.56,1:14:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...{Yoisho?}
Dialogue: 10,1:15:01.75,1:15:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:16.48,1:15:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We let Hanaguro out onto the water \Nto start flight practice.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:20.60,1:15:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But he just won't take off.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:27.34,1:15:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:28.36,1:15:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:29.86,1:15:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:30.93,1:15:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:31.89,1:15:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:33.23,1:15:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:44.87,1:15:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like I'm racing Hanaguro myself.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:49.45,1:15:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you lose.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:06.01,1:16:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! This time, fly!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:08.01,1:16:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Kick the water harder!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:11.20,1:16:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:14.02,1:16:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:16.47,1:16:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:17.74,1:16:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:20.04,1:16:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:21.21,1:16:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{disappointment}
Dialogue: 10,1:16:26.35,1:16:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What, again? But it was so close.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:28.70,1:16:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I'm worn out now!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:30.52,1:16:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, please... \NWe're flying today, no matter what! {and I don't care}
Dialogue: 10,1:16:35.52,1:16:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't take to the sky soon, \Nit'll be impossible this year.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:39.23,1:16:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it'll still take a day or two.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:51.17,1:16:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's trying again!
Dialogue: 10,1:16:52.64,1:16:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hopeless anyway. Even if {\i1}I{\i0} try \Nto keep up with it, my body won't hold out. {??? idk what he means, this TL is literal}
Dialogue: 10,1:17:00.78,1:17:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro did it!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:08.04,1:17:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro flew!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:10.78,1:17:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,1:17:14.56,1:17:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 10,1:17:22.66,1:17:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:31.98,1:17:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Way to go, Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:18:11.69,1:18:15.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro will soon return north.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:15.22,1:18:17.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dad, please get better soon too.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:17.81,1:18:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I mustn't lose either.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:21.43,1:18:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Hanaguro, who learned to fly \Nthanks to Goichi and Yuki,
Dialogue: 10,1:18:26.10,1:18:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come back restored to perfect health.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:32.01,1:18:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, Hanaguro hardly ever comes back here.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:35.95,1:18:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at night, it's with the other swans.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:39.95,1:18:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It lived apart from others for so long. \NBeing with the flock again must be fun.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:45.39,1:18:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's kind of unfriendly. {cold}
Dialogue: 10,1:18:46.76,1:18:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Like he's forgotten all about us.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:49.26,1:18:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably busy \Ngetting ready to head north.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:52.66,1:18:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 10,1:18:55.16,1:19:01.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And then, on one especially \Nwarm and cozy night...
Dialogue: 10,1:19:06.16,1:19:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans sure are noisy tonight.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:09.54,1:19:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe Hanaguro's crying with them.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:12.16,1:19:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're heading north.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:15.22,1:19:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans are?
Dialogue: 10,1:19:16.68,1:19:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's finally time to go back north. \NI can tell by that call.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:21.76,1:19:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're heading north?
Dialogue: 10,1:19:23.96,1:19:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The swans are going back \Nto the Prince's country.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:28.66,1:19:34.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just like Grandma said, \Nthe swans' journey has begun.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:37.84,1:19:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so it's finally time? \NYuki-chan, is Hanaguro there too?
Dialogue: 10,1:19:42.24,1:19:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, over there.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:49.43,1:19:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro... are you leaving?
Dialogue: 10,1:19:52.15,1:19:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, this is how it should be.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:54.26,1:19:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro's setting off \Non a long, hard journey now.
Dialogue: 10,1:19:57.49,1:20:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's pray he can keep up safely \Nwith the other swans.
Dialogue: 10,1:20:01.46,1:20:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good idea.
Dialogue: 10,1:20:03.03,1:20:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it'd be nice \Nif it looked back just once.
Dialogue: 10,1:20:15.39,1:20:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When they take off, it will.\N I'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 10,1:20:18.45,1:20:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It knows we're here, right?
Dialogue: 10,1:20:20.02,1:20:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:20:26.44,1:20:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro! Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:20:30.23,1:20:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:20:31.64,1:20:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:20:36.04,1:20:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Hanaguro.
Dialogue: 10,1:20:55.00,1:20:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro's taking off!
Dialogue: 10,1:21:16.61,1:21:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,1:21:21.23,1:21:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep trying, Hanaguro! \NWhat's wrong with you?!
Dialogue: 10,1:21:24.51,1:21:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Its wings are still weaker \Nthan the others. It can't keep up.
Dialogue: 10,1:21:34.12,1:21:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What, no good?
Dialogue: 10,1:21:50.19,1:21:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Hanaguro did it!
Dialogue: 10,1:22:09.59,1:22:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What happened?
Dialogue: 10,1:22:26.96,1:22:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{cries of happiness}
Dialogue: 10,1:22:35.80,1:22:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, Hanaguro came back \Nto say goodbye to us.
Dialogue: 10,1:22:40.64,1:22:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:22:45.91,1:22:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:22:54.37,1:22:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, this is it. {the end/final meeting}
Dialogue: 10,1:22:56.61,1:22:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch it carefully.
Dialogue: 10,1:23:04.30,1:23:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro!
Dialogue: 10,1:23:08.52,1:23:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro! Goodbye!
Dialogue: 10,1:23:13.96,1:23:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly strong and stay well!
Dialogue: 10,1:23:17.76,1:23:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it all the way \Nto the Prince's northern land!
Dialogue: 10,1:23:27.49,1:23:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,1:23:32.24,1:23:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro...
Dialogue: 10,1:23:59.13,1:24:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanaguro'll surely find \Na nice mate up north.
Dialogue: 10,1:24:03.97,1:24:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And have some cute little cygnets. {???}
Dialogue: 10,1:24:07.14,1:24:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then next time, they'll come back \Ntogether as a family.
Dialogue: 10,1:24:20.32,1:24:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You all stay well! \NAnd come again next year!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.24,0:41:52.68,Song,,0,0,0,,Bathed in dazzling morning light {most likely 友よはばたけ by 川島和子; no trace of lyrics, translating by ear}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.68,0:42:00.87,Song,,0,0,0,,Your eyes began to shine
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.87,0:42:09.26,Song,,0,0,0,,Do your best, wings, and spread wide {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.26,0:42:18.07,Song,,0,0,0,,Do your best, fly away into the wide sky
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.07,0:42:26.63,Song,,0,0,0,,The Prince smiles warmly
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.73,1:25:08.47,ED,,0,0,0,,Through raging blizzards {most likely 雪国の王子さま by Kawashima Kazuko; still no trace of a release outside this show, translating by ear}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.67,1:25:15.78,ED,,0,0,0,,In the season of swirling snow
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.28,1:25:28.79,ED,,0,0,0,,They come flying across the open sky
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.42,1:25:36.06,ED,,0,0,0,,No matter how painful things get
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.06,1:25:42.57,ED,,0,0,0,,They carry courage and hope
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.57,1:25:57.05,ED,,0,0,0,,And nurture the lives of tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.52,1:26:14.54,ED,,0,0,0,,White and beautiful companions
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.14,1:26:29.55,ED,,0,0,0,,Winter is cold and harsh
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.55,1:26:36.26,ED,,0,0,0,,But let's do our best and aim for spring
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.26,1:26:42.70,ED,,0,0,0,,Together, in friendship and good health
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.70,1:26:58.35,ED,,0,0,0,,Spreading our wings toward tomorrow
